## 1️⃣ Role‑Based Authorization (Very Common in Enterprise Apps)

### ✅ Problem

Different components should render based on user role.

### ✅ Currying Solution

```js
const hasRole = role => user =>
  user.roles.includes(role);

const isAdmin = hasRole("admin");
const isManager = hasRole("manager");
```

### ✅ Usage in React

```jsx
{isAdmin(user) && <AdminPanel />}
{isManager(user) && <ManagerPanel />}
```

✅ Reusable logic  
✅ Clean declarative JSX  
✅ Easy to test

***

## 2️⃣ Typed Dispatch Helpers (Redux / useReducer)

### ✅ Problem

Avoid repeating action types everywhere.

### ✅ Currying Action Creators

```js
const createAction = type => payload => ({
  type,
  payload
});

const addTodo = createAction("ADD_TODO");
const removeTodo = createAction("REMOVE_TODO");
```

### ✅ Usage

```js
dispatch(addTodo("Learn React"));
dispatch(removeTodo(3));
```

✅ Cleaner than inline objects  
✅ Reduces bugs from typos  
✅ Interview‑friendly pattern

***

## 3️⃣ Dynamic Validation Logic (Forms)

### ✅ Problem

Different fields have different validation rules.

### ✅ Curried Validators

```js
const minLength = min => value =>
  value.length >= min;

const required = () => value =>
  value.trim().length > 0;
```

### ✅ Usage

```js
const validatePassword = minLength(8);
validatePassword("secret123"); // ✅ true
```

✅ Highly reusable  
✅ Easy to compose

***

## 4️⃣ API Permission Guards

### ✅ Problem

You want to protect API calls based on permissions.

### ✅ Curried API Guard

```js
const withPermission = permission => apiFn => (...args) => {
  if (!user.permissions.includes(permission)) {
    throw new Error("Unauthorized");
  }
  return apiFn(...args);
};
```

### ✅ Usage

```js
const deleteUser = withPermission("DELETE_USER")(apiDeleteUser);
```

✅ Clean business rules  
✅ Easy to reuse across app

***

